  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Study on Assistive Technologies and Economic Opportunities for People with Disabilities in South Asia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This research would ensure six DFID country offices in the region
(Afghanistan, Bangladesh, Burma, India, Nepal and Pakistan) have
evidence to develop programmes for improving opportunities for people..
These areas have been regionally identified as priorities. This research
could also form an evidence base for mainstreaming in programmes
initiatives that are inclusive of people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With a focus on six countries of South Asia, this research would bring
evidence in each of the six countries on:
a. Effective interventions for creating economic opportunities for people
with disabilities
b. The current status of access to ATs and the diversity of policies and
practices that enable its availability and accessibility</narrative>
  </description>
